<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Berthemy</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-06-10"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Herewith I have the honor to inclose for
                            your information, and that of the government which you represent, a
                            transcript of the correspondence<note n="*" xml:id="d226fn1">For
                                inclosure see correspondence with the Chinese embassy.</note>
                            relative to the recent reception of the Chinese embassy by this
                            government.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my very high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Berthemy</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                                    &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>